Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
comparePinAssignStatistics(25.10)            comparePinAssignStatistics(25.10)

Name
       comparePinAssignStatistics  - Generates a pin QoR comparison file based
       on a reference and a target pin QoR file

Syntax
       comparePinAssignStatistics

       [-help]

       [-ignoreMinWireLength <minWireLength>]

       [-outFile <pinQoRCompareFileNam> <e>]

       -reference <referenceFileName>-target <targetFileName>

       Generates a pin QoR comparison file based on a reference and  a  target
       pin QoR file.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each comparePinAssignStatistic  parameter.  For  a
              detailed  description  of the command and all of its parameters,
              use the man command:

              man comparePinAssignStatistic.

       -ignoreMinWireLength <minWireLength>
              Specifies the minimum wire length. If reference wire length at a
              partition pin is less than the <minWireLength>, then it  is  not
              reported in the output file.

              Default: 60

              Data_type: string, optional

       -outFile <pinQoRCompareFileNam> <e>
              Specifies an output file for the pin QoR comparison.

              Default: ./qor_compare.txt

              Data_type: string, optional

       -reference <referenceFileName>
              Specifies  the  reference  file generated using the reportPinAs-
              signStatistics command. For example, the following command  gen-
              erates a reference pin QoR file named pin_qor_reference.txt.

              reportPinAssignStatistics -outFile pin_qor_reference.txt

              Data_type: string, required

       -target <targetFileName>
              Specifies  the  target file generated using the reportPinAssign-
              Statistics command. For example, the following command generates
              a target pin QoR file named pin_qor_target.txt.

              reportPinAssignStatistics -outFile pin_qor_target.txt

              Data_type: string, required

Example
       The  following  command  generates  a    pin   QoR   comparison   file,
       pin_qor_compare.txt:

       reportPinAssignStatistics -outFile pin_qor_reference.txt

       reportPinAssignStatistics -outFile pin_qor_target.txt

       comparePinAssignStatistics   -reference  pin_qor_reference.txt  -target
       pin_qor_target.txt -outFile pin_qor_compare.txt

